This test case is expected to make the (merged) ontology INCONSISTENT once
premises.ttl is loaded and reasoned over. A conformant OWL 2 DL reasoner
MUST report the ontology as inconsistent.

Construct under test : owl:disjointUnionOf
Why                   : DisjointUnion_Person is the disjoint union of Man
                        and Woman, which forces Man and Woman to be
                        pairwise disjoint, but DisjointUnion_Sam is
                        asserted a member of both.

scripts/run_all_tests.py detects this file and, instead of checking
expected-entailments.ttl, asserts that reasoning over premises.ttl raises
an inconsistency.
